The paper deals with planning in rich domains using Description Logic (DL) based Dynamic Knowledge Bases, which is a topic related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of DL also suggests a connection to Logic (cs.LO) and Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. The paper proposes a new algorithm for planning that involves both backward and forward search, which is a topic related to Planning (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
